      "socratic_hint": "The student described an animal, creature, or fictional being as their customer. Redirect gently: animals don't make purchasing decisions — if they're selling pet products, who actually pays? The owner. Ask them to rewrite the niche with the real human customer (e.g. 'pet owners who...' instead of 'dogs who...')."
