    {
      "id": "NR013",
      "name": "Pure copycat — no differentiation",
      "type": "blacklist",
      "terms": [
        "exactly like amazon", "just like amazon", "basically amazon", "same as amazon",
        "exactly like uber", "just like uber", "basically uber", "same as uber",
        "exactly like airbnb", "just like airbnb", "basically airbnb", "same as airbnb",
        "exactly like ebay", "same as ebay", "just like ebay",
        "same as shopify", "exactly like shopify",
        "copy of amazon", "copy of uber", "copy of airbnb", "copy of ebay",
        "clone of amazon", "clone of uber", "clone of airbnb",
        "exactly the same as", "a clone of", "a copy of",
        "identical to", "replica of"
      ],
      "severity": "warning",
      "flag": "pure_copycat",
      "message": "Copying an existing platform is a starting point, not a strategy. What would make your version better for your specific customer — faster, more local, more personal? A real business needs a reason for customers to choose you over the original.",
      "socratic_hint": "The student is describing a direct copy of an existing major platform. Ask: what does the big version get wrong for your specific customer? That gap — the thing the original misses — is your differentiation. Can they name one specific frustration a user of that platform has?"
    },
    {
      "id": "NR014",
      "name": "Price is the entire value proposition",
      "type": "blacklist",
      "terms": [
        "cheaper than everyone", "cheaper than everyone else", "cheapest option",
        "the cheapest", "cheapest in", "lower price than", "most affordable option",
        "half the price of", "underprice everyone", "beat every price",
        "beat their prices", "undercut everyone", "sell cheaper than",
        "sell for less than everyone", "always the lowest price",
        "free version of", "free alternative to"
      ],
      "severity": "warning",
      "flag": "price_only_niche",
      "message": "Price alone is not a niche — a bigger competitor will always beat you on price eventually. What else do you offer that they can't easily replicate? Think about convenience, personalisation, speed, or a specific skill.",
      "socratic_hint": "The student's entire value proposition is being cheap. Ask: what happens when a bigger business decides to undercut your price? What is the non-price reason your specific customer would choose you? Even one quality, speed, or service difference changes the answer."
    },
    {
